stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, June 7 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
James Laurin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MAGIC-LATE-NIGHT (Los Angeles) _ Showtime is returning to L.A. _
only on a different court. This time Earvin ``Magic'' Johnson,
businessman and AIDS activist, is host of a new late-night talk
show, and he has new teammates. By Keith Marder. (Will also move in
the ``s'' sports and ``e'' entertainment news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-06-98 1221EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19980606.0067 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
