   But nervous or not you're talking to a man who never gives up.
He led the Lakers to five National Basketball Association
championships, fought back HIV to the point that it is undetectable
in his blood and has brought jobs to the inner city with a national
chain of movie theaters, the first opening in 1995 in L.A.'s
Crenshaw district.
</P>
<P>
   Now his success will be measured in Nielsen Ratings as his show
