   (NYT7) PESHAWAR, Pakistan -- June 6, 1998 -- PAKISTAN-GUNTRADE,
6-6 -- Gun dealers in Peshawar show their wares. Peshawar has long
been a place where gunsmiths have passed along the skills to make
exact duplicates of firearms. In bazaars and along roads leading
north toward the Hindu Kush mountains and the foothills of the
Himalayas, hundreds of shops offer a dazzling array of firearms.
Many of the weapons sold here find their way into neighboring
Afghanistan, where war has been raging almost continually for more
than two decades and seems unlikely to end soon. (New York Times
Photo)
</P>
