part of its new owners' plan for speeding the area's recovery and
turning it into a year-round attraction for shoppers and a
destination for restaurant- and entertainment-seekers. Critics
contend that the ``new face'' for the center will not only
transform its retail stores, but also its landmark architecture.
(Nancy Siesel/New York Times Photo)
