   CUP-REGIS _ When Frenchman David Regis was sworn in as a U.S.
citizen earlier this month to become eligible to play in the World
Cup, he used a route not unfamiliar to soccer players in this
country: through marriage to an American woman. His connection is
the former Nikki Fogle of an Atlanta suburb. She met and married
Regis, currently a player in the German Bundesliga, three years ago
while working in France. U.S. Soccer officials first approached him
in April about obtaining citizenship, and they have been on a
whirlwind ever since. Regis is certain to be a starter in defense
for the Americans when they open their World Cup schedule with
Germany on June 15 in Paris. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 30.
