<P>
   RAMSEY _ While Colorado police are eager to have a grand jury
address the JonBenet Ramsey case, hoping it will force testimony
from those resistant to talk, at least one legal expert believes
the move will probably solve nothing and could end the
investigation. ``I don't see it (a grand jury) getting much from
any suspect,'' said William Pizzi, a former federal prosecutor and
a criminal law professor at the University of Colorado Law School.
In fact, should the process add nothing to the case, Pizzi believes
the grand jury may decide no charges are warranted. ``This may be
the last chapter'' of the story, said Pizzi. (Schneider, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
