<HEADLINE>
HARSHBARGER WINS NARROW PARTY ENDORSEMENT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By FRANK PHILLIPS  
 AND JILL ZUCKMAN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WORCESTER, Mass. _ Attorney General Scott Harshbarger
consolidated his status as the Democrats' front running
gubernatorial candidate when he very narrowly won the party's
convention endorsement Saturday with a first ballot victory over
two opponents.
</P>
<P>
   Harshbarger, who had come to the convention the heavy favorite
to win the contest, squeaked to victory by two votes out of 3,898
cast. He received 50.05 percent of the vote _ just barely the
majority necessary to win the endosement on the first ballot, but
ahead of former Senator Patricia McGovern who received 31.35
percent of the vote. Former US Representative Brian J. Donn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
