<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CUP-INTERNET-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    World Cup on the internet
 &HT;    By David Davidson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's a list of sites that should provide dozens of hours of
entertainment to the dedicated devotee of the World Cup:
</P>
<P>
   _ Yahoo, the Web browser folks, also has a killer World Cup site
_ available in nine languages. It may be the best of all.
</P>
<P>
   http://soccer.yahoo.com/wc98
</P>
<P>
   _ Budweiser is sponsoring a contest on ESPN's SportsZone similar
to the NCAA Tournament contest sponsored by Pizza Hut, which drew
250,000 entries. Entrants pick the two teams which advance from
each of the eight zones, then complete the 16-game bracket. First
prize is a giant, can-shaped Bud refrigerator.
</P>
<P>
   http://ESPN.SportsZone.com
</P>
<P>
   /soccer/worldcup98/index.html
</P>
<P>
   _ CNN/SI is another super site that will provide serious World
Cup coverage, and Time magazine has a well organized, easy to use
site, also.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.cnnsi.com/soccer
</P>
<P>
