<SLUG> BC-SOC-WORLDCUP-A-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WORLD CUP TEAMS: GROUP A 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRAZIL
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 49-13-11. Only team to appear in all 15 previous
World Cup finals and only four-time champion. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: Winner in 1958, 1962, 1970 and 1994. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Ronaldo, the best striker and, for many,
the best player in the world. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Roberto Carlos, a fleet left fullback
who has a wicked way with a free kick; Cafu, his counterpart at
right fullback, and attacking midfielders Rivaldo, Denilson and
Giovanni. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: Semifinalist. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: The Brazilians are the last non-European team to win
the World Cup in Europe, prevailing in Sweden in 1958. But in this
tournament, night matches and cooler temperatures will allow the
Europeans to apply constant pressure defensively.
</P>
<P>
   NORWAY
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 1-1-2. Two appearances in 1938 and 1994.
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: First round.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Tore Andre Flo, who plays in England and
whose nickname at home is ``Flonaldo.''
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Central defenders Ronny Johnsen and
Henning Berg and midfielders Erik Mykland and Kjetil Rekdal.
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: Quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: The Norwegians aren't telegenic but they have a good
habit of bringing out the worst in their opponents, including
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTLAND
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 4-6-10. Appearances in 1954, 1958, 1974, 1978, 1982,
1986 and 1990.
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: First round.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Attacking midfielder John Collins. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Striker Kevin Gallacher and midfielder
Paul Lambert, one of seven players who works for Celtic in the
Scottish first division.
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: First round. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: Though it is exceedingly tough to score on Scotland,
the Brazilians and Norwegians should succeed.
</P>
<P>
   MOROCCO
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 1-3-6. Three appearances in 1970, 1986 and 1994. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: Second round in 1986. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Central defender Noureddine Naybet, who
plays in the Spanish first division. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Striker Salaheddine Bassir, attacking
midfielder Mustapha Hadji and left fullback Abedlkrim El Hadrioui. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: First round. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: A disappointing African Nation's Cup didn't help Coach
Henri Michel's popularity. Failing to reach the second round won't
help his job security.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
