<HEADLINE>
WORLD CUP TEAMS: GROUP G 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ENGLAND &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 18-11-12 in nine appearances. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: Winner (as hosts) in 1966. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Striker Alan Shearer, who was once the
world's most expensive player and has now recovered from a major
ankle injury. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Goalkeeper David Seaman, right fullback
Gary Neville, midfielders David Beckham and Paul Ince and
18-year-old striker Michael Owen, the youngest player on England's
national team this century.
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: Quarterfinals. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: England was once considered a possible champion, but
its stock has dropped. It lacks a creative force in midfield _ Paul
Gascoigne failed to keep Coach Glenn Hoddle's confidence and was
dropped. Hoddle made headlines at home _ not always a good idea in
tabloid land _ for revealing recently that he and his players had
seen a spiritual healer. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ROMANIA
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 6-7-4 in six appearances. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: Quarterfinalist in 1994. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Midfielder and playmaker Gheorge Hagi,
now 33 who was one of the stars of the last World Cup. His skills
have eroded slightly, but he still has one of the game's best
sobriquets: The Maradona of the Carpathians. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Right fullback Dan Petrescu, defensive
midfielder Gheorghe Popescu and strikers Viorel Moldovan and Adrian
Ilie. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: Second round. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: The Romanians are seeded first in this group, and they
qualified smoothly, but their tension-filled preparations and Coach
Anghel Iordanescu's conflicts with the Romanian federation may have
hurt morale. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 2-6-2 in three appearances. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: Second round in 1990. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Midfielder Carlos Valderrama, 36, an
Major League Soccer employee in good standing with Miami who
apparently neglected to pay his taxes when he worked in France. The
host nation demanded payment. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Central defender Ivan Cordoba,
midfielders Harold Lozano and Freddy Rincon and striker Faustino
Asprilla. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: First round. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: This star-crossed team is in too difficult a group to
change its luck. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TUNISIA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CUP RECORD: 1-1-1 one appearance. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEST RESULT: First round. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER YOU MIGHT KNOW: Jose Clayton, a naturalized Brazilian. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PLAYERS YOU SHOULD KNOW: Central defender Ferid Chouchane,
midfielders Zoubeir Beya and Skander Souayah and striker Adel
Sellimi. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PROJECTED FINISH: First round.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENT: The large Tunisian population in France could give them
a slight home-field feeling, but the cheering will stop by the end
of the first round. This team lacks offensive punch.
</P>
