<SLUG> BC-UTAH-MANHUNT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SEARCH WIDENS FOR ARMED FUGITIVES  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By JO THOMAS   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BLANDING, Utah _ As the trail of two armed fugitives seemed to
grow cold, a massive search was expanded east and west on Saturday
to include 100 square miles in the Four Corners area of Utah,
Colorado, Arizona, and New Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   About 500 police officers and National Guardsmen, as well as
Navajo Nation police officers and trackers, are searching the
desert canyons here for Alan Pilon, 30, of Dove Creek, Colo., and
Jason Wayne McVean, 26, of Durango, Colo.
</P>
<P>
   The men, who have been described as survivalists, are suspects
in the killing of one police officer and the injuring of three
others.
</P>
<P>
   Sheriff Jerry Martin, of Dolores County, Colo., said that the
search, which has centered on the town of Bluff, Utah, has been
expanded to the west near Mexican Hat, Utah, and east to include
southwest Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   As evening approached, police checked spotlights on a bridge
over the San Juan River just south of Bluff. Navajo Police Officer
Charles Smith Jr. said the landscape south of town, much of it on
the reservation, was ``inaccessible all of the time.''
</P>
<P>
   The hunt began in Cortez on May 29, when a police officer, Dale
Claxton, 35, was shot to death with a machine gun by three hooded
men dressed in camouflage.
</P>
<P>
   Two Montezuma County, Colo., sheriff's deputies were injured in
the chase and shootout that followed. The gunmen, who had been
stopped for driving a stolen water truck, fled on foot after
leaving the truck near the entrance to three canyons in the
Hovenweep National Monument.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you had 100 men and three weeks, you could search one of
them,'' said Martin, who has a five-man force.
</P>
<P>
   The search moved to Bluff on Thursday when Kelly Bradford, 35, a
San Juan County sheriff's deputy, was shot while investigating a
report that a man in camouflage had shot at a social worker.
</P>
<P>
   At a campsite near this spot, a third suspect, Robert Matthew
Mason, 26, of Durango, was found dead, shot between the eyes. ``All
indications are suicide,'' said Sheriff Mike Lacy of San Juan
County.
</P>
<P>
   The search is ``kind of a waiting game,'' Smith said. ``You try
to figure out: What would I do if I was a bad guy? Where would I
go?''
</P>
<P>
   ``But we've got time on our side,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
